\b Using the Serial Port Inspector
\b0 \
\
The Serial Port Inspector, pictured below, provides several useful features.  Besides the Port Address and IRQ Level controls, there are two pop-up lists.\
\
Picking an entry from the Port pop-up will change the Port Address and IRQ Level selections to match the COM port you selected.  Likewise, changing either the Port Address or IRQ Level selections will change the selection of the Port pop-up accordingly.  The Custom selection is present to allow non-standard settings.\
\
The Connect Via pop-up lets you specify the type of device being used.  If a port is being configured for a PCMCIA serial device, choose "PCMCIA Modem".  For all non-PCMCIA devices, choose  "PnP Serial Port" for PnP capable devices, otherwise choose "Serial Port". \

